==============================================================================
  Q(x) POLYNOMIAL STRUCTURE — ROOTS, FACTORS, AND THE x=2 MIRACLE
==============================================================================

╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  PART 1: ALL Q(x) POLYNOMIALS FOR n ≤ 6                                     ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝


========================================================================
n = 3:
========================================================================

  H=1, α=[1], #cycles=0
  I(CG,x) = 1
  Q(x) = 0
  Q(2) = 0

  H=3, α=[1, 1], #cycles=1
  I(CG,x) = x + 1
  Q(x) = -x*(x - 2)*(x + 1)
  Q(2) = 0
  Real roots: -1.0000, 0.0000, 2.0000
  (x-2) DIVIDES Q! Quotient = -x*(x + 1)

========================================================================
n = 4:
========================================================================

  H=1, α=[1], #cycles=0
  I(CG,x) = 1
  Q(x) = 0
  Q(2) = 0

  H=3, α=[1, 1], #cycles=1
  I(CG,x) = x + 1
  Q(x) = -x*(x - 2)*(x + 1)
  Q(2) = 0
  Real roots: -1.0000, 0.0000, 2.0000
  (x-2) DIVIDES Q! Quotient = -x*(x + 1)

  H=5, α=[1, 2], #cycles=2
  I(CG,x) = 2*x + 1
  Q(x) = x*(x**3 - 2*x**2 + 4*x + 4)
  Q(2) = 24
  Real roots: -0.6850, 0.0000

